      "id": "PopularPost231031",
      "post_content": "I love the rules text of the German blackborder version.\n  \n   \nIt literally translates back to:\n  \n   \nA target which is disitegrated suffers X points of damage. Should the ensorcelled creature be destroyed in the same turn, it is removed from the game.\n  \n   \nFurthermore, taking the English version literally, a player in a multiplayer match is exiled if suffering lethal damage. ;)",
